---
title: "Data Visualization and Economic Analysis"
collection: teaching
type: "Graduate course (MA level)"
permalink: /teaching/2020-fall-teaching-ECON334
venue: "Simon Fraser University, Department of Economics"
date: 2020-09-01
location: "British Columbia, Canada"
---

How can we recognize and learn from patterns in data to add value to a firm or to design more effective economic and social policy? The objective of this course is to learn to use modern statistical software (R) to manage, visualize, and analyze data to answer real-world economic questions.
